 for bestpractices and # Notifications & Alerts

## Overview
Develop a comprehensive Notifications & Alerts system for LifeOps that supports in-app, email, and push notifications across run outcomes, approvals, anomalies, and alerts. Include digesting (batched summaries) and snoozing (deferral) capabilities, delivery retry logic, localization and templating, user preferences, and a robust audit trail. Integrate with a Master Dashboard (page_master_dashboard_006) and two associated pages: Approvals Queue (page_approvals_queue_009) and Settings (page_settings_026) to manage channels, digests, snooze rules, and templates. The system must be resilient, type-safe, and guard against runtime nulls, undefined values, and non-array data as per the mandatory coding standards.

Key goals:
- Reliable multi-channel delivery (in-app, email via SendGrid, push via Firebase) with per-user preferences
- Digest scheduling, snooze rules, and delivery retry with dead-letter outcomes
- Flexible templates with variables, localization, and runtime data safety
- Approvals workflow integration for scheduled cron actions, including rationale, diffs, comments, and conditional approvals
- A Master Dashboard that surfaces global alerts, next cron runs, active statuses, and quick-access workflows
- Full audit trail, run artifacts, and reversible actions
- Strong UI/UX consistent with the given visual style and design system

---

## Components to Build

1) Notifications Engine (Core Service)
- Responsibilities:
  - Channel-abstraction layer: in-app, email (SendGrid), push (Firebase)
  - User preferences per channel (opt-in/opt-out, digest frequency, quiet hours)
  - Digest scheduling: batch events into digest runs with per-user windows
  - Snooze rules: allow per-notification snooze with duration and conditions
  - Delivery retry policy with backoff, exponential retry, and dead-letter reporting
  - Localization and templates: support variables, localization keys, and runtime data injection
  - Audit trail: event history per notification (action, outcome, channel, timestamps, user)
- Data flow:
  - Input events (run outcome, approval required, anomaly, alert)
  - Enrichment with user preferences and localization
  - Draft notification payloads per channel
  - Dispatch with retry handling
  - Digestable aggregation per digest window
- Safety:
  - All consumer-facing data paths guarded for nulls; data defaults to arrays when iterating
  - Use Array.isArray checks and data ?? [] patterns
- APIs:
  - createNotificationEvent(event)
  - scheduleDigest(userId, notificationBundle)
  - sendNotification(notificationPayload)
  - snoozeNotification(notificationId, duration)
  - retryFailedDeliveries()

2) In-App Notification UI (Frontend)
- Pages/Widgets:
  - Notifications Center panel in the Master Dashboard
  - Per-event cards with summary, details, and action (Acknowledge, Snooze, View)
  - Digest view: collapsed digest groups with quick-browse
  - Filters: by channel, status, date, agent, and severity
- Features:
  - Real-time or near-real-time updates (WebSocket/long-poll)
  - Mark as read/unread, archive, search
  - Bulk actions for digests
  - Tooltips and contextual help
  - Accessibility: keyboard navigable, screen-reader friendly
- Data handling:
  - Graceful loading states; guards against null data
  - Use useState<T[]>([]) for arrays; initialize with proper types
  - Always treat API results as data ?? [] and verify Array.isArray before map
- UI Behavior:
  - Card design per design system: elevated, rounded, with subtle borders and shadows
  - Hover/focus interactions; clear affordances for snooze/dismiss
  - Inline templates for common actions

3) Email Notification System (Backend)
- Templates:
  - Email templates with variables, localization keys, and per-user language
  - Support for digest emails (daily/weekly/monthly) with per-notification details
- Delivery:
  - Use SendGrid integration; handle retries and failure reporting
  - Backoff policy and dead-letter notifications to admin
- Data:
  - Email address, preferred language, timezone, digest preference
- Endpoints/Jobs:
  - enqueueEmailNotification(userId, payload)
  - renderTemplate(templateId, data, locale)
  - handleEmailDeliveryStatus(webhook)
- Safety:
  - Validate payloads; guard against missing variables
  - Null-safe access to nested objects
  - Data normalization: ensure arrays treated as arrays (data ?? [])
- API surface:
  - GET /notifications/emails/pending
  - POST /notifications/emails/send
  - Webhook: POST /notifications/emails/status

4) Push Notifications (Backend + Client)
- Service:
  - Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) integration for push tokens
  - Per-user preferences: enabled/disabled, quiet hours, digest participation
- Delivery:
  - Immediate vs. digest push options
  - Retry and failure telemetry
- Client:
  - Service worker/push handler to display in-app banners and system notifications
  - Dismiss/acknowledge actions within the app
- Data:
  - Push tokens, platforms, device metadata
- Safety:
  - Guard all token accesses; ensure null-safe flows (tokens ?? [])
- Endpoints:
  - POST /notifications/push/send
  - POST /notifications/push/acknowledge

5) Approvals Queue Page (Frontend: page_approvals_queue_009)
- View:
  - List of scheduled cron actions requiring approvals
  - Diff view, agent rationale, diffs, and related artifacts
  - Accept/Reject actions with optional comments
  - Conditional approvals (based on user constraints)
- Details:
  - Per-item details panel: inputs for comments, decision, and conditional triggers
  - Audit trail of approvals
- Interactions:
  - Sorting, filtering by cron name, next run, urgency
  - Save comments and decisions; trigger subsequent actions
- Data handling:
  - Guard arrays; ensure operations on arrays are safe (Array.isArray)
- State:
  - useState<ApprovalItem[]>([]) with safe defaults
- API surface:
  - GET /approvals/queue
  - POST /approvals/queue/:id/approve
  - POST /approvals/queue/:id/reject
  - POST /approvals/queue/:id/conditional-approve

6) Master Dashboard (Frontend: page_master_dashboard_006)
- Features:
  - Global search across agents, runs, and notifications
  - Quick command bar for run actions (start/stop cron, pause digest, subscribe to channels)
  - Active cronjobs snapshot: next run, last run outcome, per-run details
  - Cross-module alerts: badge counts, recent anomalies, run outcomes
  - Quick-access workflows: templates, approvals, digests, templates for notifications
- UI:
  - Card-based overview with strong visual hierarchy
  - Right-rail widgets for digest status and recent alerts
- Data:
  - Pull in notifications, cron statuses, and alerts from Notification Engine
- Safety:
  - Ensure null-safe rendering; default to empty arrays where needed
- Interaction:
  - Real-time or near-real-time updates; quick filters and drill-downs

7) Settings & Templates Page (Frontend: page_settings_026)
- Features:
  - Channel configuration (in-app, email, push) with per-user preferences
  - Digest schedule setup (cron vs time-based windows)
  - Snooze rules editor (duration, conditions)
  - Notification templates editor with variables and localization keys
  - Validation and preview
- Data:
  - Template store with locale mapping; fallback behavior
- Safety:
  - Immutable previews; avoid undefined template fields
- API surface:
  - GET/PUT /settings/notifications
  - GET/PUT /templates/notifications
  - POST /templates/notifications/preview

---

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Architecture:
  - React (TypeScript) with a modular component library aligned to the design system
  - State management: React Query or SWR for data fetching; global state with context for user preferences
  - Hooks: useArraySafe hook patterns to ensure safe mapping over data (e.g., const safeList = Array.isArray(list) ? list : [])
- Components to build:
  - NotificationCenter: header, digest summary, per-event cards
  - DigestPanel: grouping of notifications by digest window
  - NotificationCard: icon, title, meta, action menu (Acknowledge, Snooze, View)
  - ApprovalsQueueView: list, diff panel, rationale, decision controls
  - MasterDashboardWidgets: cron snapshot, alerts, search bar, quick command bar
  - TemplatesEditor: template editor with localization keys and variable placeholders
  - SettingsKiosk: channel toggles, digest rules, snooze rules
  - Toasts/Modals for actions and confirmations
- Data safety:
  - All arrays and API responses must be guarded: (data ?? []) and Array.isArray checks
  - Initialize useState for arrays: useState<MyType[]>([])
  - Optional chaining for nested API responses: apiResponse?.payload?.items
  - Destructure with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}
- Accessibility:
  - ARIA labels, keyboard navigation, and semantic HTML
- Localization:
  - i18n ready; templates with placeholders; locale-aware rendering
- Performance:
  - Pagination or virtualization for long notification lists
  - Debounced search; minimize re-renders

### Backend
- APIs and microservices:
  - Notification Service: multi-channel dispatcher
  - Digest Scheduler: cron-based or window-based digest bundling
  - Template Service: localization and rendering
  - Email Service: SendGrid integration with status/webhook handling
  - Push Service: FCM integration with token management
  - Approvals Service: queue management, rationale management, conditional approvals
  - Cronjobs Service: schedule creation/updates, trigger logic, input payloads, constraints, safety rails, retry policy
- Data models (MSSQL/Postgres or chosen DB):
  - users(id, email, locale, timezone, preferences JSONB, push_tokens JSONB, ... )
  - notifications(id, user_id, channel, template_id, payload JSONB, status, digest_id, created_at, persisted_at, read_at, snoozed_until, retry_count, last_error)
  - digests(id, user_id, window_start, window_end, delivered_at, status)
  - templates(id, name, locale, subject, body, variables JSONB, last_modified)
  - channels(user_id, in_app, email, push, digest_enabled, digest_frequency, quiet_hours)
  - approvals_queue(id, cronjob_id, requestor_id, rationale, status, comments, created_at, updated_at, diff_blob)
  - cronjobs(id, name, enabled, schedule_expression, timezone, trigger_type, target, input_payload JSONB, permissions, constraints JSONB, safety_rails JSONB, retry_policy JSONB, outputs JSONB, next_run_at, last_run_at, last_run_status)
  - audit_logs(id, user_id, action, object_type, object_id, metadata JSONB, timestamp)
- Business logic:
  - Per-user digest batching with respect to timezone and locale
  - Retry/backoff policies with dead-letter routing
  - Template rendering with variable substitution and localization
  - Validation: strict schema validation for all API inputs
  - Security: enforce authentication and authorization; restrict access to users based on roles
- Validation:
  - All API responses validated; e.g., const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
- Data safety:
  - nullish checks for all optional fields; guard against null data in all endpoints

### Integration
- Data flow orchestration:
  - Event sources (run outcomes, anomalies, scheduled cron actions) push to Notification Engine
  - Engine enriches events with user preferences and templates, then dispatches via channels
  - Digest Scheduler batches events per user and sends digest notifications
  - Alerts feed Approvals Queue when approvals are required
  - Master Dashboard queries consolidated statuses and surfacing alerts
- Consistency:
  - All modules use consistent data structures for notifications and digests
  - Central audit logs for all user actions and system events
- Security and compliance:
  - OAuth2/JWT authentication; role-based access for Approvals, Settings, and Master Dashboard
  - Data access controls per tenant/account
- Observability:
  - Centralized logging and metrics for delivery success/failure, retries, digest generation, and snoozes
  - Tracing across agent-to-agent messages in cronjobs

---

## User Experience Flow

1) User Preference Setup
- User visits Settings > Notifications
- Configures channels: in-app, email, push
- Sets per-channel preferences: digest frequency, quiet hours, retry limits
- Creates localization preferences (default locale) and template defaults

2) Event Occurrence
- An event occurs (run outcome, anomaly, or approval requirement)
- Notification Engine evaluates user preferences and creates notification payloads
- If digest mode is enabled, event is queued for digest window; otherwise immediate delivery

3) Delivery & Snooze
- Notification is dispatched to all subscribed channels
- User receives in-app banner/toast, email, and/or push notification
- User can Snooze or Acknowledge from in-app notification
- Snooze defers delivery for a configured window; snoozed items appear in digest or re-delivery

4) Approvals Queue (for scheduled cron actions)
- Cronjob scheduled requests appear in Approvals Queue with diffs and agent rationale
- Approver reviews details, optionally adds comments, and decides Approve/Reject
- Conditional approvals may trigger alternate flows
- Approved actions proceed; rejected actions generate notes and audit trails

5) Master Dashboard Interaction
- User uses global search to locate notifications, cronjobs, or approvals
- Quick command bar enables rapid actions (e.g., pause digest, reschedule cron)
- Active cronjobs snapshot shows next run times and recent outcomes
- Cross-module alerts are surfaced with status chips and trend indicators

6) Templates & Templates Editor
- User edits templates with placeholders and localization keys
- Preview renders sample data for current locale
- Saving updates templates, affecting future deliveries

7) Admin/Settings
- Admin configures channel capabilities, template mappings, and digest rules
- Any change propagates to subsequent notification deliveries and templates

---

## Technical Specifications

Data Models: Schema details (high level)
- users: id (PK), email, locale, timezone, preferences (JSONB), push_tokens (JSONB), created_at, updated_at
- notifications: id (PK), user_id (FK), channel, template_id, payload (JSONB), status (enum: pending, delivered, failed, snoozed, read), digest_id (FK), created_at, persisted_at, read_at, snoozed_until, retry_count, last_error
- digests: id (PK), user_id (FK), window_start, window_end, delivered_at, status
- templates: id (PK), name, locale, subject, body, variables (JSONB), last_modified
- channels: id (PK), user_id (FK), in_app, email, push, digest_enabled, digest_frequency, quiet_hours
- approvals_queue: id (PK), cronjob_id (FK), requestor_id (FK), rationale, status (enum: pending, approved, rejected, conditional), comments, created_at, updated_at, diff_blob
- cronjobs: id (PK), name, enabled, schedule_expression, timezone, trigger_type, target, input_payload (JSONB), permissions (JSONB), constraints (JSONB), safety_rails (JSONB), retry_policy (JSONB), outputs (JSONB), next_run_at, last_run_at, last_run_status
- audit_logs: id (PK), user_id (FK), action, object_type, object_id, metadata (JSONB), timestamp

API Endpoints (Routes and methods)
- POST /notifications/events
  - Body: { eventType, data, userIds, channels? }
- GET /notifications/users/{userId}/preferences
- PUT /notifications/users/{userId}/preferences
- POST /notifications/digests/schedule
- GET /notifications/digests/{digestId}
- POST /notifications/digests/{digestId}/send
- POST /notifications/snooze
- POST /notifications/resend/{notificationId}
- GET /approvals/queue
- POST /approvals/queue/{id}/approve
- POST /approvals/queue/{id}/reject
- POST /approvals/queue/{id}/conditional-approve
- GET /templates
- GET /templates/{id}
- POST /templates
- PUT /templates/{id}
- GET /settings/notifications
- PUT /settings/notifications
- POST /settings/templates/preview
- POST /notifications/push/send
- POST /notifications/push/acknowledge
- Webhooks: /external/email/status, /external/push/status

Security
- Authentication: OAuth2 / JWT with per-tenant scoping
- Authorization: RBAC for Approvals (approve/reject), Settings, and Master Dashboard
- Data access controls: tenant-scoped queries; ensure no cross-tenant data leakage
- Validation: strict input shapes; all responses validated
- Data integrity: audit trails for all write actions
- Rate limiting and circuit breakers on external channels (email, push)

Validation
- All API responses validated against schemas
- Use data ?? [] patterns for Supabase-like results; Array.isArray guards for arrays
- Access nested data with optional chaining
- Destructuring with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}

---

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] All notification channels (in-app, email, push) can be configured per user, with per-channel digest preferences and quiet hours
- [ ] Digest scheduling correctly batches events per user and sends consolidated notifications without duplication
- [ ] Snooze functionality defers notifications and re-delivers as appropriate (digest or immediate) with accurate silence windows
- [ ] Delivery retry logic executes with exponential backoff and reports failures to a dead-letter path; retries do not cause crashes or undefined behavior
- [ ] Localization and templating render correctly for at least 2 locales; variables are substituted safely
- [ ] Approvals Queue page shows diffs, agent rationale, and supports approve/reject with comments; conditional approvals execute correctly
- [ ] Master Dashboard displays next cron run, active statuses, cross-module alerts, and quick-access workflows with real-time/up-to-date data
- [ ] All front-end components guard against null/undefined values; arrays initialized with proper useState([]); all API responses validated
- [ ] UI adheres to the provided design system: colors, typography, spacing, card design, navigation, and data visualization guidelines
- [ ] End-to-end tests cover: notification creation, digest sending, approval flow, and dashboard summaries

---

## UI/UX Guidelines

Apply the project’s design system exactly:
- Color Palette, Typography, Layout, and Key Design Elements (Card Design, Navigation, Data Visualization, Interactive Elements)
- Dark UI with high contrast for text, restrained accents for alerts
- 8px baseline grid; content gutters; 56–64px header; 220–260px sidebar
- Card padding 16–20px; iconography with frosted monochrome icons
- Data visualizations with subtle gridlines and restrained color palette
- Focus states, hover lifts, and tactile affordances for critical actions (approve/reject)
- Accessibility and keyboard navigation throughout

