## Technical Specifications

Data Models: Schema details (high level)
- users: id (PK), email, locale, timezone, preferences (JSONB), push_tokens (JSONB), created_at, updated_at
- notifications: id (PK), user_id (FK), channel, template_id, payload (JSONB), status (enum: pending, delivered, failed, snoozed, read), digest_id (FK), created_at, persisted_at, read_at, snoozed_until, retry_count, last_error
- digests: id (PK), user_id (FK), window_start, window_end, delivered_at, status
- templates: id (PK), name, locale, subject, body, variables (JSONB), last_modified
- channels: id (PK), user_id (FK), in_app, email, push, digest_enabled, digest_frequency, quiet_hours
- approvals_queue: id (PK), cronjob_id (FK), requestor_id (FK), rationale, status (enum: pending, approved, rejected, conditional), comments, created_at, updated_at, diff_blob
- cronjobs: id (PK), name, enabled, schedule_expression, timezone, trigger_type, target, input_payload (JSONB), permissions (JSONB), constraints (JSONB), safety_rails (JSONB), retry_policy (JSONB), outputs (JSONB), next_run_at, last_run_at, last_run_status
- audit_logs: id (PK), user_id (FK), action, object_type, object_id, metadata (JSONB), timestamp

API Endpoints (Routes and methods)
- POST /notifications/events
  - Body: { eventType, data, userIds, channels? }
- GET /notifications/users/{userId}/preferences
- PUT /notifications/users/{userId}/preferences
- POST /notifications/digests/schedule
- GET /notifications/digests/{digestId}
- POST /notifications/digests/{digestId}/send
- POST /notifications/snooze
- POST /notifications/resend/{notificationId}
- GET /approvals/queue
- POST /approvals/queue/{id}/approve
- POST /approvals/queue/{id}/reject
- POST /approvals/queue/{id}/conditional-approve
- GET /templates
- GET /templates/{id}
- POST /templates
- PUT /templates/{id}
- GET /settings/notifications
- PUT /settings/notifications
- POST /settings/templates/preview
- POST /notifications/push/send
- POST /notifications/push/acknowledge
- Webhooks: /external/email/status, /external/push/status

Security
- Authentication: OAuth2 / JWT with per-tenant scoping
- Authorization: RBAC for Approvals (approve/reject), Settings, and Master Dashboard
- Data access controls: tenant-scoped queries; ensure no cross-tenant data leakage
- Validation: strict input shapes; all responses validated
- Data integrity: audit trails for all write actions
- Rate limiting and circuit breakers on external channels (email, push)

Validation
- All API responses validated against schemas
- Use data ?? [] patterns for Supabase-like results; Array.isArray guards for arrays
- Access nested data with optional chaining
- Destructuring with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}

